17. Germany, sensing its advantage slipping, tries to lock in its gains with a peace deal, but the Allies vow to fight until victory is won.
16. US, preoccupied with policing its border with a Mexico torn by revolution, re-elected Wilson under the slogan "he kept us out of war".
15. Germany has held back on submarine warfare, keeping US neutral. Americans have prospered supplying food and material to warring Europe.
14. All warring nations are suffering food shortages, but as winter takes hold, Germany is beginning to starve, unrest is growing in Russia.
13. An entire British-Indian army was forced to surrender to the Turks after a lengthy siege at Kut, in Iraq. But the Brits would be back.
12. The Arab sheik of Mecca rebelled against his Turkish overlords, with British aid, as France & Britain schemed to divide up Middle East.
11. Irish nationalists staged a failed but heroic Easter Rising in Dublin, whose legend would lay the foundation for later independence.
10. Romania entered the war on side of the Allies, only to find itself quickly invaded and occupied by the Central Powers.
9. Neutral Greece descended into civil war as an occupying Allied army held the line in Macedonia.
8. Air warfare came into its own in 1916, with celebrated fighter aces dogfighting to control the skies over Verdun and the Somme.
7. Though the Allies saw horrific losses on the Somme, for little gain, they learned key lessons, and introduced a new weapon: the tank.
6. In August, the British and French launched their own major offensive along the Somme, hoping for a breakthrough to end the war.
5. The Italians launched several fruitless offensives against the Austrians, along their common border, but failed to make any headway.
4. A huge Russian offensive, under General Brusilov, nearly smashed through the Eastern Front, but failed to take Austria out of the war.
3. The British navy "won" the Battle of Jutland, off the Danish coast, losing more ships but keeping the German navy off the high seas.
2. Germany's failed attempt to "bleed France dry" by attacking Verdun turned into perhaps the longest and bloodiest battles yet in history.
1. So what happened in 1916? Three massive offensives (Verdun, Brusilov, Somme) and two revolts (Irish, Arab) + side show in the Balkans.
